This was the best duck we ever had. One modification we made was to roast the duck slowly: 250 degrees for about 3 hours (less with convection or speed bake) turning it twice, then at 425 for 30-45 minutes, turning once, to brown it. This duck came out crispy on the outside, moist and tender on the inside. It went great with champagne for New Year's eve, but a gewurtz would work also.

